title: South Korea 20 Year bond Yield
description: South Korea 20 Year Bond Yield was 3.90 percent on Friday November 11, according to over-the-counter interbank yield quotes for this government bond maturity. Historically, the South Korea 20 Year bond Yield reached an all time high of 6.17 in September of 2008. This page includes a chart with historical data for South Korea 20Y.
